/shrug The way that I look at it is this. At higher levels (ie. post 55) -
<br />

<br />
Wizards and druids can quad kite for decent xp in quite a few zones.
<br />
If something can be snared and doesn't summon, a necro can solo it.
<br />
Enchanters can do some crazy things with charm.
<br />
Beastlords can solo very steadily on mid level db mobs, for decent xp in the long run.
<br />
Monks, rogues, and warriors can't solo if their lives depended on it.
<br />

<br />
Bards can swarm kite and solo faster then any single class in the game. They can chant kite as well. They are the only class that can kill 50 mobs at once.
<br />

<br />
I don't know, saying there's nothing wrong with a single class being able to utterly dominate content designed around multiple groups with very little risk (and there is little risk once you get half way decent at it), seems short sighted to me.
<br />

<br />
Think of it this way - Let's say a bug is introduced where the Harm Touch ability of an SK acts as a death touch on mobs. HT Quarm - dead. If SoE removes this, is it suddenly a nerf? Would people be considered whiners if they posted saying Harm Touches should be changed back? I mean, yeesh, it's only 1 mob killed every 72 minutes. How is that overpowering??? Damn whiners.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />It's easy to use - if you're one of the 2% of the population who thinks logically and can read an instruction manual. The other 98% of the population would find it very hard or impossible to use.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
